# Vanilla SPA (KISS)

- One **hash router** in [`src/app/router.js`](src/app/router.js); routes change state, **without** re-mounting the entire view tree on every `hashchange` (single main view mount).
- Views in `src/app/views/` export `mountX(root, opts)` returning `{ unmount() }`; clean up listeners, `ResizeObserver`, and subscriptions in `unmount`.
- App state in [`src/app/state.js`](src/app/state.js): small API (`getState`, `subscribe`, `set…`), no framework.
- One responsibility per file; avoid global variables outside the state module and router.
